               <head>Six works on Sufism</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85100085 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>A collection of six works by Mīr Ḥusaynī-i Sādāt-i Haravī (d. ca. 729/1338). Although his writings have been little studied and he is best known as the writer whose questions inspired the composition of Maḥmūd Shabistarī’s great metaphysical poem Gulshan-i rāz, Mīr Ḥusaynī ranks among the more influential Persian Sufi authors of the 8th/14th century. Followed by (f. 106v), a poem in Ottoman Turkish, evidently in the riq‘ah hand of its author (li-katibih al-faqīr), commemorating the completion of a new house, and with the date 1191/1777-8 recorded in abjad.</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="5r">ff 1v-5r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659039.0x000001 viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659039.0x000001 viaf_9681161763145322560004" type="supplied">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22088">Panj ganj</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22088">پنج گنج </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Five qaṣīdahs on mystical and metaphysical themes. </p>
                        <p>Munzavī in FNKhF IV, pp. 2678-9 lists only three manuscripts of this work, all from the 9th/15th century, in Tehran, Paris and Cairo.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item2">
                     <locus from="5v" to="6r">ff 5v-6r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ara" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004" type="supplied">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9310">Qalandarnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ara" key="work_9310"> قلندرنامه </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A short Sufi poem. </p>
                        <p>FNKhF IV, p. 3049, lists three copies, including BL Add. 7611, of which only the Paris BnF manuscript predates the present one.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian. </textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item3">
                     <locus from="6v" to="60r">ff. 6v-60r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004" type="supplied">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1706"> Ṭarab al-majālis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1706"> طرب المجالس </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A prose treatise on Sufism and ethics, comprising five sections (qism) subdivided into faṣls. </p>
                        <p>For a  description of its contents and references to 13 manuscripts, see FNKhF IV, pp. 1275-6.
</p>
                        <p> The manuscript contains three contemporary miniature paintings, illustrating passages from Ṭarab al-majālis, on folios 30v, 32v, and 36r; these are of reasonably good quality but appear to have been needlessly retouched with brown paint, rather to their detriment.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item4">
                     <locus from="60v" to="74r">ff 60v-74r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317
								</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8732">
                        <addName>
                           <addName>
                              <addName>
                                 <addName/>
                              </addName>
                           </addName>
                        </addName>Kanz al-rumūz 
                     </title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8732"> کنز الرموز </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A masnavī poem concerning various aspects of the Sufi journey to God. Munzavī FNKhF IV, pp. 3060-2 lists 36 copies.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian. </textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item5">
                     <locus from="74v" to="91r">ff 74v-91r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004" type="supplied">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20102">Zād al-musāfirīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20102"> زاد المسافرين </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>
A didactic poem on aspects of the Sufi Path, comprising eight ‘discourses’ (maqāla). </p>
                        <p>FNKhF IV, pp. 2849-51 lists 42 copies including BL Sloane 3587 and Add. 16832, to which should be added Add. 7767, Add. 19809, and Or. 1226. The incipit in the present manuscript is the second of the two cited by Munzavī, loc. cit.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian. </textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Or_15964-item6">
                     <locus from="91v" to="106r">ff. 91v-106r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">Mīr Ḥusaynī Haravī, Ḥusayn ibn ʻĀlim, 1272 or 1273-approximately 1317
								</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_9681161763145322560004">مير حسينى هروى، حسين بن عالم</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>A masnavī poem, also known by the title <title>‘Ishq-nāmah</title>, comprising letters between a lover and his Beloved. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Munzavī FNKhF IV, pp. 2931-2, lists 8 copies. The incipit in the present manuscript is the second of the two cited by Munzavī, loc. cit.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22089">Sī nāmah</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian.</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
